1316
01:27:49,750 --> 01:27:52,191
a really good way to represent a long-distance relationship.

1317
01:27:53,291 --> 01:27:56,573
Because if you have a piece of paper and you have a character on one side and a character

1318
01:27:56,593 --> 01:28:00,494
on the other, they're in two entirely different worlds and they can't get to one another.

1319
01:28:01,035 --> 01:28:05,036
But if you fold that paper, you can merge those two worlds together and create a way

1320
01:28:05,076 --> 01:28:05,857
for them to reunite.

1321
01:28:05,877 --> 01:28:10,559
And I thought this was a good representation of how it feels when you're in a long-distance

1322
01:28:10,579 --> 01:28:10,899
relationship.

1323
01:28:10,919 --> 01:28:13,540
You wish you could just take your two worlds and just mash them together and be in the

1324
01:28:13,580 --> 01:28:14,020
